A chaotic architectural blueprint of a house rendered in vintage 1950s technical illustration style, showing impossible contradictions: a structure that simultaneously has 2 and 45 bedrooms stacked in impossible Escher-like geometry, a gleaming modern aluminum exterior clashing with a rusty antique refrigerator visible through a cutaway wall, a massive Olympic swimming pool squeezed impossibly into a tiny backyard, multiple arrows and revision marks scattered across the yellowed paper, coffee stains on the edges, the blueprint half-crumpled as if someone threw it down in frustration, warm sepia tones with pops of faded blue ink, drafting tools scattered around the edges including a vintage compass and protractor
